## 01

### Putting Mastery

Learn the art of putting with techniques honed on professional tours. Our sessions focus on speed control, green reading, and pressure performance, helping you sink more putts and lower your scores.

## 02

### Short Game Wizardry

Master chipping, pitching, and bunker play with our hands-on approach. We teach versatile techniques to handle any lie, giving you the edge in the scoring zone.

## 03

### Full Swing Optimization

Build a repeatable, powerful swing with our data-driven coaching. Using video analysis and launch monitors, we refine your setup, plane, and impact for maximum distance and accuracy.

## 04

### Mental Game Coaching

Develop the mental toughness needed to perform under pressure. Learn strategies from Char’s LPGA Tour experience to stay focused and confident on every shot.

## Our Facilities, Where Champions Train

Golfy Golf Academy operates out of two premier Northern California locations, offering state-of-the-art facilities and stunning environments to enhance your learning experience.

### Old Greenwood – Tahoe

Nestled in the Sierra Nevada at Tahoe Mountain Club, Old Greenwood features championship bentgrass greens and a serene mountain setting. Perfect for immersive swing and mental game training. (Seasonal: May–October)

### Haggin Oaks – Sacramento

Sacramento’s top public golf complex, with two 18-hole courses, a driving range, and year-round access. Ideal for urban golfers seeking convenient, all-weather practice.

### Practice Greens

Both locations offer meticulously maintained putting greens, designed to replicate tournament conditions for realistic putting and short game practice.

### Technology Suite

Access cutting-edge tools like TrackMan and SAM PuttLab at no extra cost, ensuring precise feedback and measurable progress in every session.

